The evidence with the title 'Grady Judd: medical marijuana is a sham - Sun Sentinel ' says Nov 19, 2013  ... Any condition where the " use of marijuana would likely outweigh the potential health risks " of someone who claimed to be sick. This means people who alleged minor ailments such as muscle spasms , neck pain, back pain and even menstrual cramps have qualified for government sanctioned pot smoking . 
